nd 1893) and a significant tranche of village housing. The parish church of St James was rebuilt in 1846 (the 14th-century 3-stage tower survives) and contains tombs of the medieval Norton family. The village is inside the South Downs National Park; the old Meon Valley railway, closed in 1955, ran through the parish and the redundant station building survives.","character":"A protected, picture-book estate village — Picturesque-theory landscape with managed sightlines from the manor through the village to the open downland beyond. Mix of listed cottages, almshouses, the Home Farm and a small number of more recent infill houses. Quiet, very tightly managed, deeply rural.","amenities":["Rotherfield Park (Grade I-listed country house, opens for National Garden Scheme days)","Front Lodge (Grade II listed, c. 1820)","Church of St James (rebuilt 1846, retains 14th-century tower)","Almshouses (1879 and 1893, Thomas and Septimus Scott)","East Tisted Village Hall","Cricket and recreation ground","Disused Meon Valley railway line walking route"],"schools":[{"name":"Ropley Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"2.5 mi","url":"https://www.ropley.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"Amery Hill School (Alton)","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"5.5 mi","url":"https://www.ameryhill.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"Eggar''s School (Alton)","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"5.0 mi","url":"https://www.eggars.net/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 6m – 1h 18m direct","mode":"drive to Alton + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/alton-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"London Waterloo (alt.)","time":"1h 2m – 1h 17m direct","mode":"drive to Liss (~5 mi) + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/liss"}],"nearestStation":"Alton (5.0 mi)","roads":"A32 (Alton–Fareham) runs through the village; A31 (M3 to Winchester) ~5 mi north at Alton"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/gu34-3ql.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Rotherfield Park gardens (National Garden Scheme open days)","Walking on the disused Meon Valley railway line and the Shipwrights Way","Selborne and Gilbert White''s House (~3 mi)","Jane Austen''s House at Chawton (~6 mi)","Watercress Line steam railway from Alton (~5 mi)"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Pub With No Name (White Horse)","type":"Country pub with rooms","notes":"17th-century pub at Priors Dean, ~2 mi south","url":"https://www.thepubwithnoname.uk/"},{"name":"The Selborne Arms","type":"Village pub","notes":"Country pub in Selborne, ~3 mi east","url":"https://www.selbornearms.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Inside the South Downs National Park with Grade I-listed country house and Grade II-registered park on its doorstep","Two market towns within easy drive — Alton (with direct London Waterloo trains) ~5 mi north, Petersfield ~7 mi south","Strong walking infrastructure: Shipwrights Way, Hangers Way, old Meon Valley line","Picturesque, deliberately managed visual character","Cricket ground, village hall and active parish council"],"cons":["No pub or shop within the village itself — closest pub is The Pub With No Name at Priors Dean (~2 mi)","Estate ownership means open-market freehold supply is unusual; many houses are estate-tenanted","A32 runs through the village — through-traffic noise on frontages","No mainline station within walking distance; car essential","Strict SDNP and conservation-area planning constraints"],"whoItSuits":"Buyers prepared to wait for relatively scarce open-market opportunities in an estate village inside the South Downs National Park. Strong fit for retirees, country-house buyers, equestrian households, and home-workers willing to absorb the 5-mile drive to Alton or Liss for the station. Not first-time buyer territory: when freehold stock does come up, it usually sits in the country-cottage market.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Alton (5.0 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Sainsbury''s Alton (~5 mi); Waitrose New Alresford (~7 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — East Tisted","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Tisted"},{"label":"Wikipedia — Rotherfield Park","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotherfield_Park"},{"label":"Historic England — Rotherfield Park (registered)","url":"https://historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1000163"},{"label":"East Tisted Parish Council","url":"https://www.easttisted-pc.gov.uk/"},{"label":"British History Online — Parishes: East Tisted","url":"https://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/hants/vol3/pp30-35"},{"label":"South Western Railway — Alton to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/alton-to-london-waterloo"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (East Tisted parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]},{"id":"east-tytherely-sp5","name":"East Tytherely","village":"East Tytherely","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP5","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":50.99476,"lng":-1.847},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"easton-so21","name":"Easton","village":"Easton","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO21","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.08688,"lng":-1.31852},"coordsSource